&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1872.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; first population census&lt;/strong&gt; in India was conducted in &lt;strong&gt;1872.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The census was conducted during the&lt;strong&gt; British rule in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The census was conducted by &lt;strong&gt;Lord Mayo&lt;/strong&gt;, who was the &lt;strong&gt;Governor-General of India&lt;/strong&gt; at that time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The census covered only &lt;strong&gt;British-administered territories &lt;/strong&gt;and did not include princely states.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The census was conducted to gather information about the population and to understand the&lt;strong&gt; social and economic conditions &lt;/strong&gt;of the people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Population Census&lt;/strong&gt;:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A population census is a process of collecting, compiling, and publishing &lt;strong&gt;demographic, social, and economic data&lt;/strong&gt; about the people living in a&lt;strong&gt; specific geographic area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The census helps in understanding the &lt;strong&gt;size, distribution, and characteristics of the population.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The census data is used by &lt;strong&gt;governments, policymakers, researchers, and businesses&lt;/strong&gt; for planning, decision-making, and resource allocation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The population census is conducted periodically in most countries, and the data collected is used for a variety of purposes, including &lt;strong&gt;electoral representation, public health, education, and infrastructure planning.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sattriya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Her Sattriya dance is her specialty. 2015 saw Saikia win the &lt;strong&gt;Sangeet Natak Akademi Award&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The dancer received the Bishnu Rabha Award from the&lt;strong&gt; Department of Cultural Affairs&lt;/strong&gt; of the&lt;strong&gt; Government of Assam in 2022&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Guru Jatin Goswami, Guru Ghanakanta Bora, Manik and Bhabananda Barbayan, Moniram Dutta, and Dr. Bhupen Hazarika are a few of the top male Sattriya artists.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sattriya dance&amp;#39;s modern form is credited to&lt;strong&gt; Mahapurush Srimanta Sankardev&lt;/strong&gt;, who created it to go with plays used for religious instruction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The flute had been incorporated into the performance by the &lt;strong&gt;15th&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;century&lt;/strong&gt;, and Sankardev had written music specifically for the dances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the 15th century, Srimanta Sankardev began a &lt;strong&gt;neo-Vaishnavite movement&lt;/strong&gt; in Assam, which gave rise to the Sattriya sect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He spread what is known as &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;ek sharan naama dharma&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;(chanting the name of one God devotedly).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Ankiya bhaona &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;Ojapali dances&lt;/strong&gt;, in which the lead singer sings, performs abhinaya, tells stories, and a group of dancer&amp;#39;s dance as backup dancers while playing small cymbals, are both included in the corpus of &lt;strong&gt;Sattriya dances&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A significant component of&lt;strong&gt; Indian classical dance &lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt; music is ritualistic worship&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assam&amp;#39;s cultural legacy&lt;/strong&gt; is inextricably linked to the more than &lt;strong&gt;600-year-old Sattriya traditions&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;ritualistic practises &lt;/strong&gt;found in&lt;strong&gt; mediaeval Vaishnavite monasteries&lt;/strong&gt;, or sattras.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They offer a vivid view of&lt;strong&gt; Assamese culture&lt;/strong&gt; by reflecting the ancient idioms of the land and society.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Kuchipudi:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The dance-drama performance known as Kuchipudi has its origins in the &lt;strong&gt;Natya Shastra&lt;/strong&gt;, an old Hindu scripture written in Sanskrit.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Like all significant Indian classical dances, it began as a&lt;strong&gt; religious art form &lt;/strong&gt;associated with itinerant bards, temples, and spiritual beliefs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Copper inscriptions from the 10th century and manuscripts like the Machupalli Kaifat from the &lt;strong&gt;15th century &lt;/strong&gt;both contain evidence of&lt;strong&gt; Kuchipudi&amp;#39;s earlier existence&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;According to Kuchipudi tradition, the contemporary form of Kuchipudi was established and systematized in the 17th century by the &lt;strong&gt;sanyasin Tirtha Narayana Yati&lt;/strong&gt; and his student, an orphan named &lt;strong&gt;Siddhendra Yogi.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Bharatanatyam:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Indian classical dance known as bharatanatyam has its roots in &lt;strong&gt;Tamil Nadu&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It reflects South Indian religious themes and spiritual ideals, primarily those of &lt;strong&gt;Shaivism &lt;/strong&gt;and generally of &lt;strong&gt;Hinduism&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is &lt;strong&gt;one&lt;/strong&gt; of the eight Indian classical dance styles recognized by the&lt;strong&gt; Sangeet Natak Akademi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Kathak:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;One of the&lt;strong&gt; eight primary styles&lt;/strong&gt; of Indian classical dance is kathak.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is an&lt;strong&gt; Uttar Pradesh classical dance style&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The storytellers or itinerant bards known as&lt;strong&gt; Kathakars&lt;/strong&gt; in ancient northern India are often credited as the creators of Kathak.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Vedic Sanskrit words Katha, which means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;story&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and Kathakar, which means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;the one who tells a story&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;Or &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to do with stories&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; are the roots of the word Kathak.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Traveling Kathakars used dance, songs, and music to transmit tales from the &lt;strong&gt;great epics &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;ancient mythology&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Kathak dancers use &lt;strong&gt;intricate footwork&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; flexible body movements&lt;/strong&gt;, and, most importantly, &lt;strong&gt;expressive face expressions to convey a variety of stories&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is option 4. i.e. &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Giddha Dance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Giddha is a popular folk dance of women in &lt;strong&gt;Punjab &lt;/strong&gt;region of India and Pakistan where the Giddha dance is performed along with the&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;rhythmic clapping and a typical traditional folk song&lt;/strong&gt; which is sung by the aged ladies in the background.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ramlila &lt;/strong&gt;is a folk dance of &lt;strong&gt;Uttar Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt; which that shows the re-enactment of the life of Rama&amp;nbsp;according to the Ramayana as well as other related epics.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Raslila &lt;/strong&gt;is a traditional dance form of the &lt;strong&gt;Uttar Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt; which&amp;nbsp;is a form of a devotional operatic play dedicated to Krishna&amp;#39;s story depicting the Krisha&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;childhood and amorous youth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ahir Dance&lt;/strong&gt; is a very popular dance form that is famous in the State of &lt;strong&gt;Uttar Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt; as well as Madhya Pradesh in India which&amp;nbsp;draws heavily from Indian mythology and leaves audiences enchanted with the charming moves executed during it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MIzoram.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The people of Mizoram are traditionally known as the &amp;#39;Singing Tribe&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The regional folk songs of Mizoram are the richest heritage of Mizos.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Saikuti, a poetess from Mizoram, composed songs in praise of warriors, brave hunters, great warriors and young men who aspire to be hunters.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;She also praised the warriors for their achievements against their enemies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mizoram is the cradle of the folk music traditions of Saikuti Zai.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mizoram&amp;#39;s folk music consists of swaras (singing) accompanied by traditional drums, gongs and other native percussion instruments.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Flute-playing also has a long history which has now come to an end.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Drums are made from a hollow tree trunk, with a membrane made of cow hide, and clocks made of brass are similar to those found in Myanmar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Most of the Mizo musical instruments used at the time of festivals and dances are different types of khuang and striking instruments like dar, bengbung, seki, talkhuang.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mizo folk songs are named after the person. Most of them are named after the original composer of music as well as verse melodies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;White&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to The Flag Code of India 2002,&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;The Indian National flag represents the hopes and aspirations of the people of India. It is the symbol of national pride&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evolution of the Indian Flag:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1st Flag&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;It had religious symbols and eight lotus&amp;nbsp;in the green band, on top.&lt;/strong&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vande Matram wrote in the middle, in the yellow band.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At bottom: A moon, A sun, in the red band.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It was hoisted on August 7, 1906, at Parsi Bagan Square in Kolkata.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2nd Flag:&lt;/strong&gt; Hoisted in Paris by Madame Cama and her band of exiled revolutionaries in 1907.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Very similar to the first flag except the top strip had only one lotus and&amp;nbsp;seven stars denoting the Saptarishi.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;It was&amp;nbsp;exhibited at a socialist conference in Berlin.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3rd flag&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;In 1917, Dr Annie Besant and Lokmanya Tilak hoisted it during the Home rule movement.&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;It had five red and four green horizontal strips arranged alternately, with&amp;nbsp;the Saptarishi configuration super-imposed on them.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;In the left-hand top corner was the Union Jack. There was also a white crescent and star in one corner.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4th Flag&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;During the session of the All India Congress Committee in 1921 at Vijayawada. &lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A flag was brought to Gandhiji. Made up of two colours-red and green-representing the two major communities i.e. Hindus and Muslims.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gandhiji suggested the addition of a white strip to represent the remaining communities of India and the spinning wheel to symbolise progress of the Nation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5th Flag&lt;/strong&gt;: This flag, the forbear of the present one, was saffron, white and green with &lt;strong&gt;Mahatma Gandhi&amp;#39;s spinning wheel at the centre.&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;It was, however, clearly stated that it bore no communal significance. Adopted by a resolution in 1931.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6th Flag&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;On July 22, 1947, the Constituent Assembly adopted it as Free India National Flag&lt;/strong&gt;.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;After the advent of Independence, the colours and their significance remained the same.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Only the Dharma Charkha of Emperor Asoka was adopted in place of the spinning wheel as the emblem on the flag.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Union Jack&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the national flag of the United Kingdom.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Indian Home Rule movement&lt;/strong&gt; was&amp;nbsp;based on the lines of the Irish Home Rule movement.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Founder: Annie Besant.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Founded: April 1916, Belgaum.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In 1921 All India Home Rule League changed its name to Swarajya Sabha.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Kashmir Valley.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kheer Bhawani Mela:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Every year on the day of Jyeshtha Ashtami Kashmiri Pandits visits Mata Ragneya Devi Temple also known as Kheer Bhawani Temple to pay their obeisance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This year Mela was celebrated on the 28th of May with great fervor and enthusiasm by not only Kashmiri Pandits but also by the locals of the&lt;strong&gt; Kashmir valley.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Kheer Bhawani Mela held on Jyeshtha Ashtami in Kashmir occupies a sacred place in the spiritual realm of the Kashmiri Pandit sisters and brothers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1993 A.D&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;55px&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/11/6090f924894fcbf1de416379_16363625541941.png&quot; width=&quot;180px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was constituted on &lt;strong&gt;12 October 1993 &lt;/strong&gt;under the&lt;strong&gt; Protection of Human Rights&lt;/strong&gt; Ordinance of&lt;strong&gt; 28 September 1993.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;National Human&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Rights Commission (NHRC) &lt;/strong&gt;of India is an autonomous public body responsible for the protection and promotion of human rights, defined by the Act as &amp;quot;rights relating to life, liberty, equality, and dignity of the individual guaranteed by the Constitution or embodied in the International Covenants&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was given a statutory basis by the &lt;strong&gt;Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993 (TPHRA).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Its headquarters&amp;nbsp;is located in &lt;strong&gt;Sardar Patel Bhawan, New Delhi,&lt;/strong&gt; India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The NHRC consists of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chairman and Five members&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(excluding the ex-officio members).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A Chairperson, who has been a Chief Justice of India or a Judge of the Supreme Court.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;One member who is, or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court of India, or, One member who is, or has been, the Chief Justice of a High Court.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Three Members&lt;/span&gt;, out of which at least one shall be a woman to be appointed from amongst persons having knowledge of, or practical experience in, matters relating to human rights.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In addition, the Chairpersons of National Commissions viz., National Commission for Scheduled Castes, National Commission for Scheduled Tribes, National Commission for Women, National Commission for Minorities, National Commission for Backward Classes, National Commission for Protection of Child Rights; and the Chief Commissioner for Persons with Disabilities serve as ex officio members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Protection of Human Rights Act mandates the NHRC to perform the following:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactively&lt;/strong&gt; or reactively inquire into violations of human rights by the government of India or negligence of such violation by a public servant.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The protection of human rights and recommend measures for their effective implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Review the factors, including acts of terrorism that inhibit the enjoyment of human rights, and recommend appropriate remedial measures.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To study treaties and other international instruments on human rights and make recommendations for their effective implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Undertake and promote research in the field of human rights.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To visit jails and study the condition of inmates.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Engage in human rights education among various sections of society and promote awareness of the safeguards available for the protection of these rights through publications, the media, seminars, and other available means.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Encourage the efforts of NGOs and institutions congress to work in the field of human rights.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It considers the necessity for the protection of human rights.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office.&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_3253E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
